  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And the sons of Tola,.... The eldest son of Issachar, whose posterity are only reckoned by name: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Uzzi, and Rephaiah, and Jeriel, and Jahmai, and Jibsam, and Shemuel, heads of their father's house, to wit, of Tola; the principal man of his family: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "they were valiant men of might in their generations, famous for their courage and military exploits, though they sprang from Tola, whose name signifies \"a worm\"; and which name Bochart (k) conjectures was given him by his parents, because he was so weakly that they had no hopes of raising him; and yet from him sprung such mighty men, and from them such a numerous race, as follows: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "whose number was, in the days of David, two and twenty thousand and six hundred; besides those of the posterity of Uzzi, after mentioned. This was at the time Joab took the number of Israel, by the order of David, 1 Chronicles 21:5. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "whose number was, in the days of David, two and twenty thousand and six hundred; besides those of the posterity of Uzzi, after mentioned. This was at the time Joab took the number of Israel, by the order of David, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Chronicles 21:5",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(k) Hierozoic. par. 2. l. 4. c. 21. col. 630. ",
        "children": [
